Philippines Stocks: First Philippine, MacroAsia, Zeus Holdings

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-07-18T04:49:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-18/ayala-cebu-macroasia-san-miguel-philippines-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.4 percent to a
record 4,476.01.  First Philippine Holdings Corp. (FPH)  , which has
investments in energy, gained 1.3 percent to 62.05 pesos, the
steepest advance since July 4. The company bought back 129,530
of its own shares at 60.90 pesos each in the open market on July
15, a stock-exchange filing showed.  MacroAsia Corp. (MAC)  , a Philippine provider of in-
flight services, gained 1.9 percent to 3.24 pesos, the highest
close since May 2. The stock rebounded from a loss of as much as
3.1 percent earlier. Lufthansa Technik Philippines Inc., a
MacroAsia venture, will begin operating from the $30 million
extension of its aircraft maintenance and repair facility in
Manila in the first quarter of 2012, a stock-exchange filing
showed.  Zeus Holdings Inc. (ZHI)   surged 49 percent to 47
centavos after jumping the same amount on July 15. The shares
climbed to the highest close since December 2007 after the
company said in a stock-exchange filing that it’s in
“continuing” talks with owners of mining claims as it tries to
enter the mining business.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
